        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:13PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 513 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Madeline, or 12 miles north of Termo, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madeline and Blue Lake Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
